Graphical restaurant reservation system
http://www.ideaswatch.com/startup-idea/graphical-restaurant-reservation-system

A reservation system for pubs and restaurants that would allow you to see a graphical layout of the establishment. You would see what tables are available at what times and you’d be able to book a specific table for a specific time. You could do it on the web or using a mobile app without needing to call the restaurant. You  can pick your seats on a plane, why not a restaurant?

## CodeCanyon guidelines:
> Ensure your app is focused on improving workflow for developers.

Consider supporting universal and multipurpose template. In example: The layout of the menu is completely customisable (icon, titles, sections), in addition you can add as many items to the menu as you like.

Refreshing React is important!

I’ve just realized that I was already involved too far in the beginning of React in  2015 days.

Here’s recap today :
* I must collect all places and resources about React ecosystem. A better comprehensive place at https://reactjs.org
* It will need a strategic approach to rehydrate my React knowledge. In the beginning, it will better if I separate Redux first. So the difference will be clear on how I treat React with or without Redux, also it will help me to understand why there are some functions or patterns were exist in a certain way.
* Dan Abramov’s Redux courses now available for free at https://egghead.io/redux
* Thanks to Ryan Florence, co-author of React Router, for making his free Advance React course videos available at https://reacttraining.com/patterns/
* There is no perfect time to start to focus on React development rather than now. I must focus on this area since now.
* Both React and React Native is best skills as the investment for next couple of years. Its potential will help me to exist and survive for this decade.

Writing in a journal is impactful practice to incorporate into your life.
It can provide insight into:
* your deepest desires
* empower intentions.
* energy blockages
* transformation.

Every ten minutes to journal each day allows you to check in, express your emotions and redirect your focus.

This mindfulness exercise develops your ability to focus on the person moment and connect with your deeper self.

With the power of journaling, you able to re-center and keep intentions at the forefront of your mind.

Every morning, write down a small intention that is going to help you achieve a long term goal. Then before bed, check in with that day’s intention :
* What went well? 
* What did you struggle with?
* What can you change for the next day?

Noticing the things that help or prevent you having success with your intentions will direct you on your journey and change your old habits.

Energy blockages such as :
* Emotional and mental trauma
* Physical ailments
Energy blockage are created when we believe, think, or act a certain way due to things that have happened to us.

The power of journaling allows you to explore these deeply personal experiences without having to open up to others, which can be extremely therapeutic.

One of our favourite aspects of writing in a journal is simply having time dedicated to our selves each day.

Not everything you write has to be profound, eye-opening, or life-changing.

Simply writing down : 
* what happened that day
* what you are thankful for
* something that inspired you
* inspirational quote and why it resonates with you.

Writing is a personal way to track your growth. Months, or even years, down the road, you can look back on old journal posts and see how your beliefs, actions and interests have changed since your first started the journal.

> Everyday is an opportunity for self growth and exploration. Take advantage of the gift of life in the present moment and do something that fulfils you each day.
